  "The study of waste in fictional literature": "",
  "Waste characterization involves testing and analyzing waste to identify its chemical composition, physical properties, and regulatory classification. This determines the appropriate treatment, storage, and disposal methods required by law.": "",
  "A computer manufacturer produces 10 million laptops per year. Each laptop contains approximately 2 grams of gold, 30 grams of copper, and small amounts of rare earth elements. When consumers discard these laptops, most end up in landfills. What economic argument supports investing in e-waste recycling infrastructure?": "",
  "There is no economic value in recycling electronics": "",
