  "Recycling electronics is only worthwhile for rare earth elements": "",
  "E-waste recycling is only profitable in developing countries with low labor costs": "",
  "One ton of circuit boards contains approximately 40-800 times more gold than one ton of gold ore. The 10 million laptops contain about 20 metric tons of gold alone. Urban mining of e-waste recovers valuable materials while avoiding the massive environmental damage of traditional mining.": "",
  "Workers at an informal e-waste recycling operation in a developing country burn circuit boards in open pits to recover copper wire. Children play nearby while toxic smoke containing lead, mercury, and dioxins fills the air. Blood tests show dangerous lead levels in the children. What international policy failure does this scenario illustrate?": "",
