  "PFAS are only found in military applications and nowhere else": "",
  "PFAS are harmless and the 'forever chemical' name is misleading": "",
  "PFAS contain extremely strong carbon-fluorine bonds that resist degradation by biological, chemical, and physical processes, persisting indefinitely in the environment": "",
  "PFAS contain carbon-fluorine bonds, among the strongest in organic chemistry, making them virtually indestructible in the environment. They do not biodegrade, resist conventional water treatment, and accumulate in organisms, making contamination sites extremely difficult and expensive to clean up.": "",
  "A recycling program in a city of 500,000 people has a contamination rate of 25%, meaning one-quarter of items placed in recycling bins are non-recyclable. This contamination costs the city $2 million per year in processing losses and rejected loads. What strategy would most effectively reduce contamination?": "",
